---
description: Core repository rules for all Aureline work
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Aureline is an independent product; use Git HEAD and canonical docs as truth.
- Read `AGENTS.md` and check branch/status before work; preserve unrelated changes.
- Never read, expose, stage, or commit `.env` files.
- Never report PASS for validation that was not run.
- Work directly on `main` only when the task explicitly permits it; otherwise follow the documented workflow.
- Do not modify `.reference/` or add features outside the task scope.
- Keep product display naming `Aureline` and packaged executable naming `aureline.exe`.
- Use meaningful, reviewable commit messages.
